1
00:00:00,833 --> 00:00:02,333
<i>Kiko's in charge
of housekeeping.</i>

2
00:00:02,333 --> 00:00:04,433
<i>- Housekeeping?
- [BARKS MOCKINGLY]</i>

3
00:00:04,433 --> 00:00:06,000
<i>- You've got some nerve!
- What are you even saying?!</i>

4
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:09,000
<i>We'll beat them to it.
We'll make them leave.</i>

5
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,733
<i> We're stronger than them.</i>

6
00:00:10,733 --> 00:00:12,567
<i>- Okay, next, Jade will lead
- Hey!</i>

7
00:00:12,567 --> 00:00:14,567
<i>- our next stretch.
- Edward.</i>

8
00:00:14,567 --> 00:00:16,067
<i> What are you doing?</i>

9
00:00:16,067 --> 00:00:17,600
<i> Past is past.</i>

10
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:20,433
<i> Bosses, we've got a problem.</i>

11
00:00:20,433 --> 00:00:22,600
<i>Monette and I are worried
about our guest.</i>

12
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:23,733
<i> They haven't come out yet.</i>

13
00:00:23,733 --> 00:00:24,967
<i> We can report it now.</i>

14
00:00:24,967 --> 00:00:26,067
<i>Nobody's reporting this
to the police.</i>

15
00:00:26,067 --> 00:00:29,100
<i>Are you crazy?
Don't let my grandma see you.</i>

16
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:31,867
<i> I said I'd pay you, right?</i>

17
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,967
I'll head out first, Luna.

18
00:00:36,967 --> 00:00:38,833
- See you--
- Yeah, yeah.

19
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,733
Go now.
I'll follow later.

20
00:00:42,633 --> 00:00:43,667
Alright.

21
00:00:43,667 --> 00:00:44,900
Take care, okay?

22
00:00:45,833 --> 00:00:48,800
If you need daily updates
on hotel activities,

23
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:49,867
I'll just email you.

24
00:00:49,867 --> 00:00:53,900
And I'll update you
if I've talked to Edward.

25
00:00:55,033 --> 00:00:57,467
Where's Gio going?

26
00:00:57,467 --> 00:01:00,133
Don't mind him.
He's always leaving.

27
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:04,133
During work hours?

28
00:01:04,133 --> 00:01:06,100
Why?
You need him for something?

29
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:07,200
- I'll call him.
- No, no.

30
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:08,800
It's fine. It's fine.

31
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:09,967
Thank you.

32
00:01:09,967 --> 00:01:16,867
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

33
00:01:18,867 --> 00:01:21,633
- So we're good?
- Mm-hmm. Yes.

34
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:24,633
Thank you.
Just send it to my email.

35
00:01:24,633 --> 00:01:26,133
Sure.

36
00:01:26,133 --> 00:01:28,900
[MARTIN BREATHES DEEPLY]

37
00:01:28,900 --> 00:01:35,500
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

38
00:01:36,867 --> 00:01:39,700
Here.
That's an advance payment.

39
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:44,833
I shouldn't even be paying you
since I didn't sell the car.

40
00:01:44,833 --> 00:01:47,200
But it got stolen
while it was with you, right?

41
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:49,200
So you're still paying for that.

42
00:01:52,267 --> 00:01:56,167
I know it's not enough.
But I'll give the rest.

43
00:01:56,167 --> 00:01:58,867
So leave my grandma alone.

44
00:02:00,267 --> 00:02:03,000
If you don't hurry, I might
just date your grandma.

45
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,733
You ****!

46
00:02:04,733 --> 00:02:06,567
[LAUGHS]

47
00:02:06,567 --> 00:02:08,033
- Go ahead, do it!
- What?

48
00:02:08,033 --> 00:02:10,833
Do it.
Your debt's just getting bigger.

49
00:02:10,833 --> 00:02:12,800
Hope karma hits you,
you bastard.

50
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:15,567
Karma?

51
00:02:16,767 --> 00:02:20,200
Who's the one
broke right now?

52
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:27,033
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

53
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:36,833
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

54
00:03:31,367 --> 00:03:32,967
[MARTIN BREATHES SOFTLY]

55
00:03:40,933 --> 00:03:43,300
[EXHALES SHARPLY, CLEARS THROAT]

56
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:45,267
[LINE RINGING]

57
00:03:45,267 --> 00:03:46,700
Dad.

58
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:48,267
<i>When were you
planning to tell me</i>

59
00:03:48,267 --> 00:03:51,967
<i>you brought Ronald in
as an investor in your hotel?</i>

60
00:03:51,967 --> 00:03:54,767
I was going to tell you.
You just beat me to it.

61
00:03:54,800 --> 00:03:57,800
<i>What do you even know
about running a hotel?</i>

62
00:03:57,800 --> 00:04:00,967
You couldn't even keep
a simple bookstore afloat.

63
00:04:00,967 --> 00:04:03,067
And now a hotel?

64
00:04:03,067 --> 00:04:04,967
<i> I will make this work.</i>

65
00:04:04,967 --> 00:04:07,167
That's what you said before

66
00:04:07,167 --> 00:04:09,800
about that business in Manila
you wasted.

67
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:12,267
<i>That's because you never
gave me a chance to save it.</i>

68
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:17,367
Martin, there's nothing
you can do about that hotel.

69
00:04:17,367 --> 00:04:19,467
<i> You know what? Fine.</i>

70
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:23,133
<i>Since you're so confident,
go ahead.</i>

71
00:04:23,133 --> 00:04:24,867
<i> Show me what you've got.</i>

72
00:04:24,867 --> 00:04:29,033
<i>But don't you ever come
back to me asking for help.</i>

73
00:04:29,067 --> 00:04:34,000
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

74
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:38,867
<i>I'll prove to you
exactly what I'm capable of.</i>

75
00:04:44,333 --> 00:04:47,167
Oh, I know you.

76
00:04:47,167 --> 00:04:48,700
What do you need?

77
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:51,667
Sir, we'd like
to report something.

78
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,367
Oh, Kiko.

79
00:04:55,367 --> 00:04:57,133
Ah, Sir Henry.

80
00:04:58,333 --> 00:05:00,433
I'll take this.

81
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:03,067
Uh...
How can I help you?

82
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:06,033
We'd like to report something.

83
00:05:06,033 --> 00:05:08,767
One of our guests
hasn't come back yet.

84
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:10,533
We're getting worried.

85
00:05:10,533 --> 00:05:12,133
Alright, you can file a blotter.

86
00:05:12,133 --> 00:05:13,800
There's no mandatory
waiting time.

87
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,967
See? That's better, right?

88
00:05:15,967 --> 00:05:19,433
Yes, sir.
We'll file the report.

89
00:05:19,433 --> 00:05:20,733
Dela Paz?

90
00:05:21,967 --> 00:05:23,367
Yes?

91
00:05:23,367 --> 00:05:26,867
Assist them.
They have a missing guest.

92
00:05:26,867 --> 00:05:27,800
Okay.

93
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,800
Ah, Raphie...

94
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:32,433
Is it okay if
you go with Ma'am?

95
00:05:32,433 --> 00:05:34,067
You handled the check-in,

96
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:35,967
so you might be able
to answer more questions.

97
00:05:35,967 --> 00:05:37,233
Sure!

98
00:05:37,233 --> 00:05:38,900
This way.

99
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:41,767
- Thank you.
- So, ma'am, here are the...

100
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:44,267
Do you have something
to say, Kiko?

101
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:46,800
Yes, sir.

102
00:05:47,900 --> 00:05:50,567
Since I'm already here...

103
00:05:50,567 --> 00:05:53,233
I wanted to ask something.

104
00:05:53,233 --> 00:05:54,300
About what?

105
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:59,067
About my father's death.

106
00:06:00,333 --> 00:06:02,133
Let's talk inside.

107
00:06:06,567 --> 00:06:10,300
You're asking if it's possible
your father

108
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:12,067
and Frederico Almazan
didn't kill each other?

109
00:06:14,033 --> 00:06:16,100
I was just thinking...

110
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:18,233
Maybe someone else killed them?

111
00:06:19,933 --> 00:06:21,067
Maybe, sir.

112
00:06:22,433 --> 00:06:24,600
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

113
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:28,267
But based on the autopsy report
and the witness statement,

114
00:06:28,267 --> 00:06:31,800
that's what led to their deaths.

115
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:35,933
Someone saw them arguing.

116
00:06:35,933 --> 00:06:39,400
And the gun
belonged to your father.

117
00:06:41,533 --> 00:06:44,033
Is that so, sir?

118
00:06:44,033 --> 00:06:46,400
I just really don't understand

119
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:49,233
how they could've
done that to each other.

120
00:06:49,233 --> 00:06:51,133
They were friends.

121
00:06:51,133 --> 00:06:54,467
They were so close, Papa even
gave Uncle Fred a share

122
00:06:54,467 --> 00:06:56,500
in Hotel 88,
no strings attached.

123
00:06:57,533 --> 00:06:58,867
No strings attached?

124
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,133
Sir, it's nothing.

125
00:07:03,133 --> 00:07:05,633
Please don't think about it.

126
00:07:05,633 --> 00:07:10,567
You're right. There's an autopsy
and there's a witness.

127
00:07:10,567 --> 00:07:12,233
So don't worry about it, sir.

128
00:07:12,233 --> 00:07:14,033
- Sorry for the trouble.
- [KNOCKING ON DOOR]

129
00:07:14,033 --> 00:07:16,200
[DOOR OPENS]

130
00:07:16,233 --> 00:07:17,433
I'm done.

131
00:07:17,433 --> 00:07:20,333
Sir, thank you again
for your help.

132
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:22,367
Alright. Thank you, sir.
We'll go now.

133
00:07:22,367 --> 00:07:24,933
If the guest isn't back
by tomorrow, call me.

134
00:07:24,933 --> 00:07:26,400
- Okay, sir. Thank you again.
- Thank you, sir.

135
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:28,167
- Let's go.
- Coming!

136
00:07:28,167 --> 00:07:30,433
Do you need to pee?
[RAPHIE GRUNTS]

137
00:07:30,433 --> 00:07:37,333
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

138
00:07:56,767 --> 00:07:58,733
It's Edward...

139
00:08:01,867 --> 00:08:03,733
Justin, Luna,
I'm sorry I'm late.

140
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:05,800
- It's okay.
- It's alright, bro.

141
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,433
My sister and I didn't
wait long.

142
00:08:07,433 --> 00:08:08,867
Really?

143
00:08:08,867 --> 00:08:10,733
Anyways...

144
00:08:10,733 --> 00:08:13,567
Luna, is this about what
we talked about?

145
00:08:13,567 --> 00:08:15,300
The one no one is supposed
to know?

146
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:16,733
No, Edward.

147
00:08:16,733 --> 00:08:18,533
This is about
the hotel's promotion.

148
00:08:22,667 --> 00:08:24,500
That was you?

149
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:26,833
Our secretary told me,
someone called

150
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:28,900
about Hotel 88's promotion.

151
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:32,133
And they said they want
to hire me.

152
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:35,467
Are you sure?

153
00:08:35,767 --> 00:08:38,600
I know this wasn't part of what
we talked about,

154
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,433
but I need you for this.

155
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:43,267
Okay, so...

156
00:08:43,267 --> 00:08:45,600
what about the other person
who called me?

157
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:48,300
[SCOFFS] Just forget about them.

158
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:49,933
Just talk to my sister instead.

159
00:08:49,933 --> 00:08:54,767
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

160
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:56,800
Okay, then.

161
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:58,133
Tell me.

162
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:00,433
[LUNA] It's simple.

163
00:09:00,433 --> 00:09:03,933
Like I said earlier, we need
a promo for Hotel 88.

164
00:09:03,933 --> 00:09:07,333
Since you have
so many followers,

165
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:09,300
one post from you
would be a huge help.

166
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:11,333
- [SNAPS FINGERS]
- Piece of cake.

167
00:09:11,333 --> 00:09:14,633
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

168
00:09:14,633 --> 00:09:15,800
But...

169
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:17,633
I don't know anything
about Hotel 88.

170
00:09:17,633 --> 00:09:20,267
Don't worry,
someone will be joining you.

171
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:24,300
Who?

172
00:09:24,300 --> 00:09:25,567
- Me.
- Jade.

173
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:28,200
Jade is in marketing.

174
00:09:28,233 --> 00:09:30,367
It's Jade who should be
doing the work.

175
00:09:30,367 --> 00:09:35,200
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

176
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,667
I'll work with Jade.

177
00:09:37,700 --> 00:09:39,300
[CHUCKLES]

178
00:09:40,367 --> 00:09:43,700
- [JADE GROANS] Ouch!
- [LUNA] Here, use this.

179
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:47,200
Luna.

180
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,767
Will Edward really
promote the hotel?

181
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:53,900
Yes. And since
you're in marketing...

182
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:56,333
- I'll leave him to you, okay?
- [GROANS]

183
00:10:02,700 --> 00:10:04,367
Is there a problem?

184
00:10:04,367 --> 00:10:05,933
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

185
00:10:05,933 --> 00:10:07,333
Nothing at all.

186
00:10:08,867 --> 00:10:11,967
- Right there.
- Let's work on this, Jade.

187
00:10:13,367 --> 00:10:15,767
We need Edward so I can
carry out my plan

188
00:10:15,767 --> 00:10:18,500
to get those siblings
out of Hotel 88.

189
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:22,567
Huh? How?

190
00:10:23,567 --> 00:10:24,900
Just trust me.

191
00:10:25,867 --> 00:10:27,833
Just stick to the plan.

192
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,033
Please?

193
00:10:30,033 --> 00:10:32,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

194
00:10:32,667 --> 00:10:35,567
- [SIGHS] Fine.
- [CHUCKLES]

195
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:37,467
- [JADE] Ouch! Luna, it hurts!
- [LUNA GUSHES]

196
00:10:37,467 --> 00:10:39,467
- Ouch! There, there.
- Sorry, sorry.

197
00:10:39,467 --> 00:10:42,067
Please, I can't reach
this part here.

198
00:10:42,067 --> 00:10:43,867
- Where did you get that from?
- Stretching.

199
00:10:44,467 --> 00:10:46,367
Stretching? Why is your
whole back hurting?

200
00:10:50,467 --> 00:10:51,633
[SIGHS]

201
00:10:51,633 --> 00:10:52,700
- [THUD]
- Oh.

202
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:54,867
[HISSES]

203
00:10:55,900 --> 00:10:56,900
[SIGHS]

204
00:10:57,900 --> 00:10:59,233
[GROANS SLIGHTLY]

205
00:10:59,933 --> 00:11:01,433
[INHALES DEEPLY]

206
00:11:01,433 --> 00:11:02,600
[GROANS SLIGHTLY]

207
00:11:03,467 --> 00:11:04,400
[EDWARD] You ran away

208
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,400
<i>because you're
embarrassed of me</i>

209
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:06,567
<i>for what you did
to me at the--</i>

210
00:11:06,567 --> 00:11:07,700
[JADE] Really?

211
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:10,033
<i>You really want to talk
about that here?</i>

212
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:11,967
[EDWARD] But just so you know...

213
00:11:11,967 --> 00:11:12,933
[JADE] Ouch!

214
00:11:12,933 --> 00:11:14,000
[EDWARD] Past is past.

215
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:20,933
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

216
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:30,933
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

217
00:11:40,433 --> 00:11:44,633
[WHIMSICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

218
00:11:44,667 --> 00:11:51,600
["PANGHABANG IKAW"
BY DARREN PLAYING]

219
00:12:06,633 --> 00:12:13,600
["PANGHABANG IKAW" CONTINUES]

220
00:12:28,533 --> 00:12:35,467
["PANGHABANG IKAW" CONTINUES]

221
00:12:47,067 --> 00:12:48,467
<i> Move back for a bit.</i>

222
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,600
[JADE CHUCKLES]

223
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:53,367
<i> You knew it was me right away?</i>

224
00:12:56,433 --> 00:12:58,500
<i>Because you smell like
sour baby powder.</i>

225
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:00,033
[CHUCKLES] Hey!

226
00:13:00,033 --> 00:13:03,067
<i> Hey, that's too much! No way!</i>

227
00:13:03,067 --> 00:13:04,867
<i> Wait, what are you even doing?</i>

228
00:13:04,867 --> 00:13:06,833
<i>- Wait, wait.
- What's with the candy?</i>

229
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,067
<i>- Huh?
- [JAR CLICKING]</i>

230
00:13:09,067 --> 00:13:10,167
[CHUCKLES]

231
00:13:10,867 --> 00:13:12,767
- [LID CLICKS]
- [CHUCKLES] Hey.

232
00:13:12,767 --> 00:13:14,867
[LAUGHING]

233
00:13:16,033 --> 00:13:17,367
<i> Are you done?</i>

234
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:19,500
<i> Ready.</i>

235
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:21,700
<i> You're ready? Can I sit now?</i>

236
00:13:21,733 --> 00:13:24,967
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

237
00:13:24,967 --> 00:13:26,200
[CHAIR SLIDES]

238
00:13:32,067 --> 00:13:36,867
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

239
00:13:36,867 --> 00:13:37,833
[EDWARD] For you.

240
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:45,067
<i> Thank you.</i>

241
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:47,833
[CHUCKLES]

242
00:13:49,033 --> 00:13:50,800
[JADE] You did this?

243
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:57,733
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

244
00:14:12,733 --> 00:14:17,833
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

245
00:14:17,833 --> 00:14:19,067
<i> What is this?</i>

246
00:14:21,933 --> 00:14:23,000
[EDWARD] Jade, sorry.

247
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,767
<i> I don't know how to paint.</i>

248
00:14:24,767 --> 00:14:26,067
"Will you be my prom date?"

249
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:28,500
<i> But you understand, right?</i>

250
00:14:28,533 --> 00:14:31,300
["PANGHABANG IKAW"
BY DARREN PLAYING]

251
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:32,600
[CHUCKLES]

252
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:33,767
<i> Yes, Eddybear.</i>

253
00:14:40,033 --> 00:14:42,933
<i> So, what's your answer?</i>

254
00:14:44,533 --> 00:14:45,733
<i> Yes!</i>

255
00:14:46,133 --> 00:14:47,567
<i> I said it's a yes!</i>

256
00:14:47,933 --> 00:14:49,600
<i> Of course it's you!</i>

257
00:14:50,100 --> 00:14:54,833
[CHUCKLING]

258
00:14:55,700 --> 00:14:57,600
- [EDWARD CLEARS THROAT]
- Wait, are all of these yours?

259
00:14:57,600 --> 00:15:00,100
Why do you have more than I do?

260
00:15:02,533 --> 00:15:05,133
<i>Well, red is your
favorite color, right?</i>

261
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:08,633
<i> So I just chose what you like.</i>

262
00:15:10,633 --> 00:15:12,667
<i> You're so sweet.</i>

263
00:15:12,667 --> 00:15:14,200
<i> Thank you!</i> [CHUCKLES]

264
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:20,000
[DISTANT STUDENT CHATTER]

265
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:26,967
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

266
00:15:27,667 --> 00:15:29,067
[JADE CLEARS THROAT]

267
00:15:29,067 --> 00:15:30,233
<i> Uh...</i>

268
00:15:30,233 --> 00:15:33,667
<i>I need to go now,
I still have something to do.</i>

269
00:15:33,667 --> 00:15:35,000
<i> I'll get going.</i>

270
00:15:35,033 --> 00:15:36,167
<i> Where are you going?</i>

271
00:15:36,867 --> 00:15:39,167
<i>I need to go, Edward.
Thank you.</i>

272
00:15:39,167 --> 00:15:40,167
[EDWARD CLEARS THROAT]

273
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:45,933
[JADE] Hi!

274
00:15:45,933 --> 00:15:48,700
<i> Sorry... Sorry, I'm late.</i>

275
00:15:49,033 --> 00:15:50,233
[CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

276
00:15:51,833 --> 00:15:58,733
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

277
00:16:11,033 --> 00:16:12,667
[WOMAN]<i> Hey!
</i> Let's take a picture.

278
00:16:16,900 --> 00:16:18,700
<i> Uhm, excuse me?</i>

279
00:16:23,867 --> 00:16:30,767
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

280
00:16:32,233 --> 00:16:33,267
[WOMAN] Sure, let's go.

281
00:16:34,733 --> 00:16:36,100
[LINE RINGING]

282
00:16:36,100 --> 00:16:37,267
[EDWARD] Dad...

283
00:16:40,067 --> 00:16:41,200
<i> Jade isn't here yet,</i>

284
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,867
<i>but the program
is about to start.</i>

285
00:16:44,267 --> 00:16:46,833
<i>Alright, Dad,
I'll just wait for her here.</i>

286
00:16:46,833 --> 00:16:53,767
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

287
00:17:08,067 --> 00:17:15,033
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

288
00:17:17,967 --> 00:17:21,133
[DISTANT LAUGHTER]

289
00:17:21,133 --> 00:17:23,333
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

290
00:17:29,833 --> 00:17:33,767
"Will you be my prom date?"

291
00:17:34,933 --> 00:17:41,900
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

292
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:46,967
Did you really only see that?

293
00:17:46,967 --> 00:17:48,000
That was really all.

294
00:17:48,967 --> 00:17:50,767
That's also what
I told the police.

295
00:17:51,300 --> 00:17:53,200
Two men arrived...

296
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:55,033
and they got into a fight.

297
00:17:55,033 --> 00:17:57,300
When I went inside my house,

298
00:17:57,300 --> 00:17:58,767
I heard gunshots.

299
00:17:59,733 --> 00:18:01,000
When I came out, the two men

300
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:02,167
were already lying
on the ground.

301
00:18:02,167 --> 00:18:04,067
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

302
00:18:04,067 --> 00:18:06,300
That's also what
Sir Henri told me.

303
00:18:07,467 --> 00:18:09,133
I'm sorry, boy...

304
00:18:09,133 --> 00:18:11,300
but that's all I can do
for your father.

305
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:18,267
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

306
00:18:21,233 --> 00:18:22,333
[EXHALES]

307
00:18:22,900 --> 00:18:24,733
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

308
00:18:30,333 --> 00:18:34,733
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

309
00:18:34,733 --> 00:18:36,467
Ah, ma'am.

310
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:39,033
There's nothing.

311
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,267
Are you sure?

312
00:18:41,267 --> 00:18:44,000
Did you check every corner
of the car?

313
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:48,833
Yes, ma'am. I really didn't see
any jewelry there.

314
00:18:48,833 --> 00:18:50,100
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

315
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:51,500
- [SIGHS]
- But...

316
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:54,267
...if you'd like,
I can check again.

317
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:55,500
Yes, please.

318
00:18:55,533 --> 00:18:56,533
Keep checking.

319
00:18:56,533 --> 00:18:57,900
[LEON] Mom?

320
00:18:58,533 --> 00:19:00,367
[FRIDA] Leon.

321
00:19:03,467 --> 00:19:05,167
Are you having Roi
look for something?

322
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:07,267
Oh, it's...

323
00:19:08,467 --> 00:19:10,400
It's nothing.
Just a small thing.

324
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:12,000
Nothing to worry about.

325
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:15,867
Where were you? At the hotel?

326
00:19:15,867 --> 00:19:17,067
Ah.

327
00:19:17,067 --> 00:19:18,700
Uh, no, Mom. Uh...

328
00:19:19,867 --> 00:19:21,233
I just had something
to take care of.

329
00:19:22,733 --> 00:19:24,900
- I'll go to my room.
- Okay. Sure.

330
00:19:24,900 --> 00:19:31,833
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

331
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:36,200
[CROW CAWS]

332
00:19:43,967 --> 00:19:49,233
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

333
00:19:49,233 --> 00:19:56,900
[MUSIC BECOMES SUSPENSEFUL]

334
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,900
[RAPHIE] Really? Is it true?

335
00:20:01,933 --> 00:20:04,933
Yes! I even had it checked
at the pawnshop.

336
00:20:04,933 --> 00:20:06,233
They said it's expensive.

337
00:20:07,933 --> 00:20:09,933
Well then,
you should've pawned it.

338
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:12,167
Hey, why would I pawn it?
It's not mine.

339
00:20:12,167 --> 00:20:14,467
Oh, I thought it was yours.

340
00:20:14,467 --> 00:20:15,500
No.

341
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:17,800
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

342
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:19,200
[RAPHIE] So what are you
planning to do with it?

343
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:20,267
Are you going to return it?

344
00:20:20,867 --> 00:20:22,133
Finders keepers, right?

345
00:20:22,133 --> 00:20:23,033
- Just give it to me.
- Hey!

346
00:20:23,033 --> 00:20:24,500
Give it to me
if you don't want it.

347
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:26,067
[KIKO] I'll feel things
out first.

348
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:27,867
This is mine, okay?

349
00:20:27,867 --> 00:20:30,900
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

350
00:20:32,133 --> 00:20:33,300
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

351
00:20:33,767 --> 00:20:34,933
[MARTIN] Just handle
the matters here.

352
00:20:34,967 --> 00:20:36,833
I've got an important
meeting so

353
00:20:36,833 --> 00:20:37,967
just update me, okay?

354
00:20:37,967 --> 00:20:39,267
[KIKO] Okay.

355
00:20:39,667 --> 00:20:41,967
[MARTIN] Sir, Kiko will be
taking care of you.

356
00:20:41,967 --> 00:20:43,133
Okay.

357
00:20:43,133 --> 00:20:45,667
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

358
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:50,633
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

359
00:20:50,633 --> 00:20:52,267
Mr. Madrigal.

360
00:20:53,300 --> 00:20:55,600
Hi. You can just call me Martin.

361
00:20:56,967 --> 00:20:59,367
Yes, I didn't expect you'd come.

362
00:20:59,367 --> 00:21:03,367
I just wanted to pitch to you
to get you to promote our hotel.

363
00:21:03,367 --> 00:21:04,967
It's all right.

364
00:21:04,967 --> 00:21:06,867
You'll just say yes right away?

365
00:21:06,867 --> 00:21:07,700
I haven't even--

366
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:10,667
Yes, I've talked to
Luna about it.

367
00:21:11,233 --> 00:21:12,800
Did I hear it right?

368
00:21:13,733 --> 00:21:16,367
You've talked... to Luna?

369
00:21:16,367 --> 00:21:17,933
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

370
00:21:17,933 --> 00:21:19,900
[CHUCKLES] Yes, it's Luna.

371
00:21:19,900 --> 00:21:21,200
It's not easy
to reject her because

372
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:23,333
the Almazans are
friends of our family.

373
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:25,333
Okay.

374
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:28,367
Is there... a problem?

375
00:21:28,367 --> 00:21:30,167
[MARTIN] No, no! Of course not.

376
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:33,167
There's probably just
some miscommunication.

377
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:35,933
But I'm sorry if
I've bothered you.

378
00:21:35,933 --> 00:21:37,900
- No worries.
- I'll get going then.

379
00:21:38,367 --> 00:21:39,733
[EDWARD] Take care.

380
00:21:39,733 --> 00:21:46,700
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

381
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:51,400
[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

382
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:52,933
Dela Paz.

383
00:21:55,067 --> 00:21:57,867
There's a gun but
there's no papers.

384
00:21:59,367 --> 00:22:01,333
That's already questionable.

385
00:22:01,933 --> 00:22:03,333
There's only a gun?

386
00:22:03,900 --> 00:22:06,867
Why? Is there something else
that should be here?

387
00:22:07,733 --> 00:22:09,100
[KIKO STUTTERS]

388
00:22:09,100 --> 00:22:12,067
No, sir. I just thought
there's something else there.

389
00:22:13,733 --> 00:22:16,100
Okay, we'll include this
in our report.

390
00:22:16,133 --> 00:22:18,133
But we still need
to check this gun.

391
00:22:18,133 --> 00:22:25,100
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

392
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:32,367
[PLASTIC CRINKLING]

393
00:22:34,900 --> 00:22:36,567
- Martin.
- What?

394
00:22:37,733 --> 00:22:40,067
Can I give you an update,
or you're in a bad mood?

395
00:22:40,067 --> 00:22:41,767
Come on, tell me already.

396
00:22:42,633 --> 00:22:44,733
The police have left.

397
00:22:44,733 --> 00:22:47,467
They found a gun
in Jeff's possession.

398
00:22:47,467 --> 00:22:49,400
They said
it has no legal papers.

399
00:22:49,433 --> 00:22:51,800
Does it have anything to do
with his disappearance?

400
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:54,000
I don't know.

401
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,333
I don't know. But, Martin...

402
00:22:56,333 --> 00:22:58,100
I've seen that gun before, too.

403
00:22:58,100 --> 00:23:00,467
- But...
- But what?

404
00:23:00,467 --> 00:23:01,900
Kiko, tell me!

405
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:07,800
It actually came with money,
bundled in one-thousand bills.

406
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:09,133
That much?

407
00:23:09,133 --> 00:23:11,067
Yes, but they're all gone.

408
00:23:12,467 --> 00:23:15,600
What if the guest came back
without us knowing?

409
00:23:16,700 --> 00:23:18,600
I wish it were that simple.

410
00:23:19,967 --> 00:23:22,533
[SIGHS SHARPLY] But have it
checked anyway, okay?

411
00:23:22,567 --> 00:23:25,800
Check which staff came in,
just to be safe.

412
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:27,667
Our hotel's reputation
might be ruined.

413
00:23:28,867 --> 00:23:31,867
But only Gio knew about that.

414
00:23:31,867 --> 00:23:33,533
What? What did you say?

415
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:37,833
I mean, I was with Monette
in the room.

416
00:23:37,833 --> 00:23:40,000
She didn't see the money.

417
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,500
But Gio did.

418
00:23:42,500 --> 00:23:46,700
B-But I don't want
to assume anything bad about it.

419
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:49,733
But he'd always say
he needed money.

420
00:23:49,733 --> 00:23:54,900
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

421
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:56,500
[MARTIN] He's here.

422
00:23:56,533 --> 00:24:03,500
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

423
00:24:13,100 --> 00:24:14,700
[MARTIN] Let's talk!

424
00:24:14,700 --> 00:24:17,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

425
00:24:17,767 --> 00:24:19,533
About what?

426
00:24:19,533 --> 00:24:21,000
It's about money.

427
00:24:22,867 --> 00:24:24,067
What money?

428
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:26,933
The guest's money.

429
00:24:26,933 --> 00:24:33,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

430
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:35,533
<i>- One mistake...
- Martin.</i>

431
00:24:35,533 --> 00:24:38,067
<i>Legally, they will take this
all away from us!</i>

432
00:24:38,067 --> 00:24:39,900
<i> How are you and Edward?</i>

433
00:24:39,900 --> 00:24:41,733
<i>Gosh, you're so full
of yourself!</i>

434
00:24:41,733 --> 00:24:43,100
<i> Ah! Aah!</i>

435
00:24:43,100 --> 00:24:45,867
<i>Goodness, you almost broke
my earring!</i>

436
00:24:46,700 --> 00:24:47,767
<i> I know that.</i>

437
00:24:47,767 --> 00:24:48,900
<i> Which one of them?</i>

438
00:24:48,900 --> 00:24:52,067
<i> Jade, Luna, or their mother?</i>

439
00:24:52,067 --> 00:24:54,667
<i>But I think we need
to report this to the police.</i>

440
00:24:55,867 --> 00:24:57,200
<i> Something feels wrong.</i>

441
00:24:57,200 --> 00:25:00,533
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

442
00:25:00,533 --> 00:25:01,600
[GASPS]

443
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:04,567
[MUSIC FADING]

